        if (Value *V = foldAndOrOfICmps(ICmp0, ICmp1, SI, /*IsAnd*/ true,
                                        /*IsLogical*/ true)) {
          // Create select OuterCond, V, false
          return SelectInst::Create(OuterCond, V, Zero);
        }
  }
}
```

This should match our pattern! Let me check why it's not working. The issue might be that `foldAndOrOfICmps` returns `nullptr` for this case because `simplifyRangeCheck` is only called when `!IsLogical` (see line 3303 in InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp).

